builderTools.legend.ScriptedBrushPage.Title = [TMP] Scriptable Brushes
builderTools.legend.ScriptedBrushPage.Description = [TMP] This is a brush made in the Node Editor without any coding. If you want to make your own brush like this one, you can:
builderTools.legend.ScriptedBrushPage.ToolSettings = [TMP] Open the tool settings.
builderTools.legend.ScriptedBrushPage.ExampleScriptedBrush.Title = [TMP] Opening the Node Editor for Scripted Brushes:
builderTools.legend.ScriptedBrushPage.ExampleScriptedBrush.Description = [TMP] 1. Go to Assets > Asset Node Editor.\n\
2. The Node Editor tool will pop up.\n\
3. In the Node Editor, click on Root Node: Demo Workspace and select Scriptable Brush. If asked if you want to continue, say OK.\n\
4. You are now in the Scriptable Brush workspace and can make a brush!
builderTools.legend.ScriptedBrushPage.NodeEditorBasics.Title = [TMP] Scriptable Brush Node Editor Basics:
builderTools.legend.ScriptedBrushPage.NodeEditorBasics.Description = [TMP] Now that you in the workspace, you can make your brush by:\n\
- Use Right-Click to create a Node\n\
- Use Left-Click on the bubble on the created Node and drag it to the bubble on the Root Node to connect it.
4. You are now in the Scriptable Brush workspace to start making a scripted brush!
builderTools.legend.ScriptedBrushPage.NodeEditorSavingAndTesting.Title = [TMP] Saving and Testing:
builderTools.legend.ScriptedBrushPage.NodeEditorSavingAndTesting.Description = [TMP] 1. Go to File > Save or Save As, and save it to an Asset Pack.\n\
2. Go back to your game, and equip a Paint Brush Tool in your hand.\n\
4. Type in chat /sb load, and go to the brush you made.\n\
5. You can now start using your brush!

builderTools.legend.SelectTargetMaterial = [TMP] Select targeted material
builderTools.legend.AddTargetMaterial = [TMP] Add targeted material as multi-material
builderTools.legend.UndoLastBrush = [TMP] Undo last brush action
builderTools.legend.RedoLastUndo = [TMP] Redo last undone action
builderTools.legend.TipsAndTricks.Title = [TMP] Tips and Tricks
builderTools.legend.TipsAndTricks.Description = [TMP] Here are some tips and tricks for how to use this brush:
builderTools.legend.EditInventoryProperties = [TMP] Edit the brush's settings from the inventory
builderTools.legend.SettingDescription = [TMP] Below are descriptions of what each setting does for this brush:
builderTools.legend.BlockMasking = [TMP] Block Masking
builderTools.legend.BlockMaskingDescription = [TMP] Allows you to set materials to the brush that limit changes to blocks that match those materials
builderTools.legend.BlockMaskingMenuDescription = [TMP] To see all the masking options and what they do, you can:
builderTools.legend.BrushMenuMaskingTab = [TMP] Open the Brush Settings
builderTools.legend.BlockMaskingMenuTabDescription = [TMP] Open the Brush Masking Tab (near top right)
builderTools.legend.BlockMaskTarget.Title = [TMP] Mask:
builderTools.legend.BlockMaskTarget.Description = [TMP] Replace only blocks in this list
builderTools.legend.BlockMaskAbove.Title = [TMP] > Above:
builderTools.legend.BlockMaskAbove.Description = [TMP] Replace only blocks above the ones in this list
builderTools.legend.BlockMaskNot.Title = [TMP] ! Not:
builderTools.legend.BlockMaskNot.Description = [TMP] Don't replace blocks in this list
builderTools.legend.BlockMaskBelow.Title = [TMP] < Below:
builderTools.legend.BlockMaskBelow.Description = [TMP] Replace only blocks below the ones in this list
builderTools.legend.BlockMaskAdjacent.Title = [TMP] ~ Adjacent:
builderTools.legend.BlockMaskAdjacent.Description = [TMP] Replace only blocks next to the ones in this list
builderTools.legend.BlockMaskNeighbor.Title = [TMP] ^ Neighbor:
builderTools.legend.BlockMaskNeighbor.Description = [TMP] Replace only blocks touching the ones in this list

