builderTools.legend.CaveBrush.Page1.Title = [TMP] Cave Brush
builderTools.legend.CaveBrush.Page1.Description = [TMP] The Cave Brush Tool allows you to make caves and ravines.
builderTools.legend.CaveBrush.Page1.DecorateArea = [TMP] Add cave decorations where you're aiming
builderTools.legend.CaveBrush.Page1.ShapeArea = [TMP] Sculpt the cave area where you're aiming
builderTools.legend.CaveBrush.Page2.BlockTip.Title = [TMP] Customizing a Cave:
builderTools.legend.CaveBrush.Page2.BlockTip.Description = [TMP] You can customize what blocks the cave is made out of by dragging and dropping blocks from the inventory into the settings.\n\nYou can also remove blocks by double-clicking on blocks in the setting.
builderTools.legend.CaveBrush.Page2.Example1.Title = [TMP] Making and Decorating a Cave:
builderTools.legend.CaveBrush.Page2.Example1.Description = [TMP] 1. Look at the ground, the side of a mountain, or a solid chunk of land.\n\
2. Hold down the sculpt key, usually Right-Click, to start sculpting the shape of the cave.\n\
3. In the sculpted cave, look at the floor and hold down the decorate key, usually Left-Click, to add decorations.\n\
4. In the sculpted cave, look at the ceiling and hold down the decorate key, usually Left-Click, to add decorations.\n\
5. You now have a cave with decorations!
builderTools.legend.CaveBrush.Page3.Title = [TMP] Settings (1/2)
builderTools.legend.CaveBrush.Page3.CaveBlocks.Title = [TMP] Cave Blocks:
builderTools.legend.CaveBrush.Page3.CaveBlocks.Description = [TMP] - The blocks to make the cave out of.
builderTools.legend.CaveBrush.Page3.CaveBlockDecorations.Title = [TMP] Cave Block Decorations:
builderTools.legend.CaveBrush.Page3.CaveBlockDecorations.Description = [TMP] - The blocks to decorate the cave floor with on the sides of the Floor Blocks. Comes with a Density slider to control how many to place.
builderTools.legend.CaveBrush.Page3.TopDecorations.Title = [TMP] Top Decorations:
builderTools.legend.CaveBrush.Page3.TopDecorations.Description = [TMP] - The blocks to decorate the cave ceiling with. Comes with a Density slider to control how many to place.
builderTools.legend.CaveBrush.Page3.FloorBlocks.Title = [TMP] Floor Blocks:
builderTools.legend.CaveBrush.Page3.FloorBlocks.Description = [TMP] - The blocks to decorate the cave floor with. Comes with a Density slider to control how many to place.
builderTools.legend.CaveBrush.Page3.FloorDecorations.Title = [TMP] Floor Decorations:
builderTools.legend.CaveBrush.Page3.FloorDecorations.Description = [TMP] - The blocks to place as decoration on top of the Floor Blocks. Comes with a Density slider to control how many to place.
builderTools.legend.CaveBrush.Page3.OreBlocks.Title = [TMP] Ore Blocks:
builderTools.legend.CaveBrush.Page3.OreBlocks.Description = [TMP] - The ore blocks to place around the cave. Comes with a Density slider to control how many to place.
builderTools.legend.CaveBrush.Page4.Title = [TMP] Settings (2/2)
builderTools.legend.CaveBrush.Page4.Randomize.Title = [TMP] Randomize:
builderTools.legend.CaveBrush.Page4.Randomize.Description = [TMP] - When checked, makes the shape smaller or larger at random when shaping the cave.
builderTools.legend.CaveBrush.Page4.MeltStrength.Title = [TMP] Melt Strength:
builderTools.legend.CaveBrush.Page4.MeltStrength.Description = [TMP] - Controls the carving strength of the brush. Higher = removes more blocks, Lower = removes less blocks.
builderTools.legend.CaveBrush.Page4.SmoothStrength.Title = [TMP] Smooth Strength:
builderTools.legend.CaveBrush.Page4.SmoothStrength.Description = [TMP] - Controls the smoothing strength of the brush. Higher = more smooth, Lower = less smooth.

builderTools.legend.BoulderBrush.Page1.Title = [TMP] Boulder Brush
builderTools.legend.BoulderBrush.Page1.Description = [TMP] The Boulder Brush Tool allows you to make boulders and rock formations.
builderTools.legend.BoulderBrush.Page1.DecorateArea = [TMP] Decorate the boulder where you're aiming
builderTools.legend.BoulderBrush.Page1.ShapeArea = [TMP] Place a boulder where you're aiming
builderTools.legend.BoulderBrush.Page2.BlockTip.Title = [TMP] Customizing a Boulder:
builderTools.legend.BoulderBrush.Page2.BlockTip.Description = [TMP] You can customize what blocks the boulder is made out of by dragging and dropping blocks from the inventory into the settings.\n\nYou can also remove blocks by double-clicking on blocks in the setting.
builderTools.legend.BoulderBrush.Page2.Example1.Title = [TMP] Making and Decorating a Boulder:
builderTools.legend.BoulderBrush.Page2.Example1.Description = [TMP] 1. Look at the ground.\n\
2. Press the place key, usually Right-Click, to place a boulder\n\
3. Change the Origin to Center.\n\
4. Look at the boulder and press the decorate key, usually Left-Click, to add decorations.\n\
5. You now have a boulder with decorations!
builderTools.legend.BoulderBrush.Page3.Title = [TMP] Settings (1/2)
builderTools.legend.BoulderBrush.Page3.RockBlocks.Title = [TMP] Rock Blocks:
builderTools.legend.BoulderBrush.Page3.RockBlocks.Description = [TMP] - The blocks to make the boulder out of.
builderTools.legend.BoulderBrush.Page3.TopBlocks.Title = [TMP] Top Blocks:
builderTools.legend.BoulderBrush.Page3.TopBlocks.Description = [TMP] - The blocks to decorate the top of the boulder. Comes with a Density slider to control how many to place.
builderTools.legend.BoulderBrush.Page3.TopDecor.Title = [TMP] Top Decor:
builderTools.legend.BoulderBrush.Page3.TopDecor.Description = [TMP] - The blocks to place on top of the Top Blocks. Comes with a Density slider to control how many to place.
builderTools.legend.BoulderBrush.Page3.RockDecor.Title = [TMP] Rock Decor:
builderTools.legend.BoulderBrush.Page3.RockDecor.Description = [TMP] - The blocks to place on top of the Rock Blocks. Comes with a Density slider to control how many to place.
builderTools.legend.BoulderBrush.Page3.BoulderPoints.Title = [TMP] Boulder Points:
builderTools.legend.BoulderBrush.Page3.BoulderPoints.Description = [TMP] - The number of sub-boulders to use to make the boulder. The sub-boulders can be spaced with Boulder Radius to make one boulder, or a group of boulders.
builderTools.legend.BoulderBrush.Page3.BoulderRadius.Title = [TMP] Boulder Radius:
builderTools.legend.BoulderBrush.Page3.BoulderRadius.Description = [TMP] - Controls the spacing between the Boulder Points. This can be used to make the boulder wider, or create a group of boulders.
builderTools.legend.BoulderBrush.Page4.Title = [TMP] Settings (2/2)
builderTools.legend.BoulderBrush.Page4.Randomization.Title = [TMP] Randomization:
builderTools.legend.BoulderBrush.Page4.Randomization.Description = [TMP] - Controls how random the boulder looks. Higher = more random, Lower = less random.
builderTools.legend.BoulderBrush.Page4.Smoothness.Title = [TMP] Smoothness:
builderTools.legend.BoulderBrush.Page4.Smoothness.Description = [TMP] - Controls how smooth the boulder is. Higher = more smooth, Lower = less smooth.
builderTools.legend.BoulderBrush.Page4.StackSize.Title = [TMP] Stack Size (Advanced):
builderTools.legend.BoulderBrush.Page4.StackSize.Description = [TMP] - Controls how many times to stack the boulder using it's Width. This is a different way to shape boulders. The boulder will place the current shape down, move it up by the Height, decrease the Width, and place again and keep doing this.
builderTools.legend.BoulderBrush.Page4.StackRandomization.Title = [TMP] Stack Randomization (Advanced):
builderTools.legend.BoulderBrush.Page4.StackRandomization.Description = [TMP] - The randomization between the height layers of the boulder. Higher = more random, Lower = less random.
builderTools.legend.BoulderBrush.Page4.StackTip.Title = [TMP] Advanced Settings Tip:
builderTools.legend.BoulderBrush.Page4.StackTip.Description = [TMP] - To see how the Stack Size and Stack Randomization work, turn Smoothness to 0, Shape to Cube, Stack Size to above 0, and try out different Width and Heights.

builderTools.legend.BuildingBrush.Page1.Title = [TMP] Building Brush
builderTools.legend.BuildingBrush.Page1.Description = [TMP] The Building Brush Tool allows you to make buildings and form structures.
builderTools.legend.BuildingBrush.Page1.ShapeArea = [TMP] Place a building where you're aiming
builderTools.legend.BuildingBrush.Page2.BlockTip.Title = [TMP] Customizing a Building:
builderTools.legend.BuildingBrush.Page2.BlockTip.Description = [TMP] You can customize what blocks the building is made out of by dragging and dropping blocks from the inventory into the settings.\n\nYou can also remove blocks by double-clicking on blocks in the setting.
builderTools.legend.BuildingBrush.Page2.Example1.Title = [TMP] Making a Tower with Windows:
builderTools.legend.BuildingBrush.Page2.Example1.Description = [TMP] 1. Use the settings to make Width and Height to what you want.\n\
2. Change the Number of Floors to how many floors you want the tower to have.\n\
3. Change the Number of Windows to how many windows you want, and change the Window Radius so that the windows are placed properly in the wall. Windows take trial and error currently to get them placed properly in the wall.\n\
4. Change the Roof settings to be what you want.\n\
5. Press the place key, usually Right-Click, to place the building.\n\
6. You now have a tower!
builderTools.legend.BuildingBrush.Page3.Title = [TMP] Settings
builderTools.legend.BuildingBrush.Page3.MainBlock.Title = [TMP] Main Block:
builderTools.legend.BuildingBrush.Page3.MainBlock.Description = [TMP] - The main blocks to make the building out of.
builderTools.legend.BuildingBrush.Page3.SecondaryBlock.Title = [TMP] Secondary Block:
builderTools.legend.BuildingBrush.Page3.SecondaryBlock.Description = [TMP] - The blocks used as decoration across the center of the walls of the building.
builderTools.legend.BuildingBrush.Page3.FloorBlock.Title = [TMP] Floor Block:
builderTools.legend.BuildingBrush.Page3.FloorBlock.Description = [TMP] - The blocks used for the floors in the building.
builderTools.legend.BuildingBrush.Page3.EnableWindows.Title = [TMP] Enable Windows:
builderTools.legend.BuildingBrush.Page3.EnableWindows.Description = [TMP] - Enables windows to be placed on the building.
builderTools.legend.BuildingBrush.Page3.WindowRadius.Title = [TMP] Window Radius:
builderTools.legend.BuildingBrush.Page3.WindowRadius.Description = [TMP] - The radius of where the windows should be placed. This setting may take playing around with to get it right.
builderTools.legend.BuildingBrush.Page3.EnableRoof.Title = [TMP] Enable Roof:
builderTools.legend.BuildingBrush.Page3.EnableRoof.Description = [TMP] - Enables the roof to be placed on the building. Turning off the roof is good for making walls.

builderTools.legend.DecorationBrush.Page1.Title = [TMP] Decoration Brush
builderTools.legend.DecorationBrush.Page1.Description = [TMP] The Decoration Brush Tool allows you to paint decoration.
builderTools.legend.DecorationBrush.Page1.DecorateArea = [TMP] Clear blocks that match the blocks in Blocks to Clear.
builderTools.legend.DecorationBrush.Page1.ShapeArea = [TMP] Paint the decorations where you're aiming
builderTools.legend.DecorationBrush.Page2.BlockTip.Title = [TMP] Customizing the Decorations:
builderTools.legend.DecorationBrush.Page2.BlockTip.Description = [TMP] You can customize what blocks are used for the decorations by dragging and dropping blocks from the inventory into the settings.\n\nYou can also remove blocks by double-clicking on blocks in the setting.
builderTools.legend.DecorationBrush.Page2.Example1.Title = [TMP] Clearing an area and adding ground decorations:
builderTools.legend.DecorationBrush.Page2.Example1.Description = [TMP] 1. Find an area you want to add decorations.\n\
2. Hold down the clearing key, usually Left-Click, to remove blocks from the area.\n\
3. Open the settings and add any decorations you want into the settings.\n\
4. Hold down the painting key, usually Right-Click, to paint the decorations on the area.\n\
5. You have now decorated the area!
builderTools.legend.DecorationBrush.Page3.Title = [TMP] Settings
builderTools.legend.DecorationBrush.Page3.BlocksToClear.Title = [TMP] Blocks to Clear:
builderTools.legend.DecorationBrush.Page3.BlocksToClear.Description = [TMP] - The blocks to clear when using the clear blocks key, usually Left-Click.
builderTools.legend.DecorationBrush.Page3.FloorBlocks.Title = [TMP] Floor Blocks:
builderTools.legend.DecorationBrush.Page3.FloorBlocks.Description = [TMP] - The blocks to decorate with. Comes with a Density slider to control how many to place.
builderTools.legend.DecorationBrush.Page3.DecorationBlocks.Title = [TMP] Decoration Blocks:
builderTools.legend.DecorationBrush.Page3.DecorationBlocks.Description = [TMP] - The blocks to place on top of Floor Blocks. Comes with a Density slider to control how many to place.

builderTools.legend.ForestBrush.Page1.Title = [TMP] Forest Brush
builderTools.legend.ForestBrush.Page1.Description = [TMP] The Forest Brush Tool allows you to make forests and leafy brush.
builderTools.legend.ForestBrush.Page1.DecorateArea = [TMP] Add the selected decorations type where you're aiming
builderTools.legend.ForestBrush.Page1.ShapeArea = [TMP] Paints the ground where you're aiming
builderTools.legend.ForestBrush.Page2.BlockTip.Title = [TMP] Customizing a Forest:
builderTools.legend.ForestBrush.Page2.BlockTip.Description = [TMP] You can customize what blocks the forest is made out of by dragging and dropping blocks from the inventory into the settings.\n\nYou can also remove blocks by double-clicking on blocks in the setting.
builderTools.legend.ForestBrush.Page2.Example1.Title = [TMP] Making and Decorating a Forest:
builderTools.legend.ForestBrush.Page2.Example1.Description = [TMP] 1. Look at the area where you want to make the forest.\n\
2. Hold down the paint ground key, usually Right-Click, to start painting the forest floor.\n\
3. Add ground decorations by changing the type to Foliage, and adding the blocks you want to use for plants in the Foliage Blocks.\n\
4. Hold down the decorate key, usually Left-Click, to place the foliage decorations.\n\
5. Add trees by changing the type to Trees.\n\
6. Hold down the decorate key, usually Left-Click, to place the trees.\n\
5. You now have a forest!
builderTools.legend.ForestBrush.Page3.Title = [TMP] Settings
builderTools.legend.ForestBrush.Page3.NumDecorations.Title = [TMP] # of Decorations:
builderTools.legend.ForestBrush.Page3.NumDecorations.Description = [TMP] - The number of decorations to place. Only applies when the Decoration Types is set to Trees or Boulders.
builderTools.legend.ForestBrush.Page3.DecorationSpacing.Title = [TMP] Decoration Spacing:
builderTools.legend.ForestBrush.Page3.DecorationSpacing.Description = [TMP] - The spacing between decorations to be placed. Only applies when the Decoration Types is set to Trees or Boulders.
builderTools.legend.ForestBrush.Page3.FloorBlocks.Title = [TMP] Floor Blocks:
builderTools.legend.ForestBrush.Page3.FloorBlocks.Description = [TMP] - The blocks to decorate the forest floor with. Comes with a Density slider to control how many to place.
builderTools.legend.ForestBrush.Page3.FloorOutlineBlocks.Title = [TMP] Floor Outline Blocks:
builderTools.legend.ForestBrush.Page3.FloorOutlineBlocks.Description = [TMP] - The blocks to decorate the outline of the forest floor with. Comes with a Density slider to control how many to place.
builderTools.legend.ForestBrush.Page3.FloorPatchBlocks.Title = [TMP] Floor Patch Blocks:
builderTools.legend.ForestBrush.Page3.FloorPatchBlocks.Description = [TMP] - The blocks to place randomly throughout the forest floor for decoration. Comes with a Density slider to control how many to place.
builderTools.legend.ForestBrush.Page3.FoliageBlocks.Title = [TMP] Foliage Blocks:
builderTools.legend.ForestBrush.Page3.FoliageBlocks.Description = [TMP] - The blocks to use for foliage on the forest floor. Comes with a Density slider to control how many to place. Only applies when the Decoration Types is set to Foliage.

builderTools.legend.MountainBrush.Page1.Title = [TMP] Mountain Brush
builderTools.legend.MountainBrush.Page1.Description = [TMP] The Mountain Brush Tool allows you to sculpt mountains and terrain.
builderTools.legend.MountainBrush.Page1.ShapeArea = [TMP] Sculpt a mountain where you're aiming
builderTools.legend.MountainBrush.Page2.BlockTip.Title = [TMP] Customizing a Mountain:
builderTools.legend.MountainBrush.Page2.BlockTip.Description = [TMP] You can customize what blocks the mountain is made out of by dragging and dropping blocks from the inventory into the settings.\n\nYou can also remove blocks by double-clicking on blocks in the setting.
builderTools.legend.MountainBrush.Page2.Example1.Title = [TMP] Making a Mountain:
builderTools.legend.MountainBrush.Page2.Example1.Description = [TMP] 1. Look at the ground.\n\
2. Customize the blocks to use for the mountain by placing blocks in the Layer settings.\n\
3. Hold down the sculpt key, usually Right-Click, to start sculpting the shape of the mountain.\n\
4. You now can sculpt mountains!
builderTools.legend.MountainBrush.Page2.Example2.Title = [TMP] Making a Valley:
builderTools.legend.MountainBrush.Page2.Example2.Description = [TMP] 1. Look at the ground.\n\
2. Change the Number of Points to 1, and Point Spacing to above 40.\n\
3. Hold down the sculpt key, usually Right-Click, to start sculpting. Notice that you now have 2 places where the terrain is being formed.\n\
4. Sculpt in a straight line moving up and down to build up a cliff on both sides.\n\
5. You now can sculpt a valley! This ability can also be used to make multiple mountains or details in the mountains at the same time.
builderTools.legend.MountainBrush.Page3.Title = [TMP] Settings
builderTools.legend.MountainBrush.Page3.TopLayer.Title = [TMP] Top Layer:
builderTools.legend.MountainBrush.Page3.TopLayer.Description = [TMP] - The blocks that will be on the top of the terrain.
builderTools.legend.MountainBrush.Page3.MiddleLayer.Title = [TMP] Middle Layer:
builderTools.legend.MountainBrush.Page3.MiddleLayer.Description = [TMP] - The blocks that will be in the middle of the terrain.
builderTools.legend.MountainBrush.Page3.BottomLayer.Title = [TMP] Bottom Layer:
builderTools.legend.MountainBrush.Page3.BottomLayer.Description = [TMP] - The blocks that will be on the bottom of the terrain.
builderTools.legend.MountainBrush.Page3.NumberOfPoints.Title = [TMP] Number of Points:
builderTools.legend.MountainBrush.Page3.NumberOfPoints.Description = [TMP] - The number of points to use to sculpt the mountains.
builderTools.legend.MountainBrush.Page3.PointSpacing.Title = [TMP] Point Spacing:
builderTools.legend.MountainBrush.Page3.PointSpacing.Description = [TMP] - The spacing between the Number of Points used to sculpt the mountain.
builderTools.legend.MountainBrush.Page3.Smoothness.Title = [TMP] Smoothness:
builderTools.legend.MountainBrush.Page3.Smoothness.Description = [TMP] - Controls how smooth the sculpted terrain will be. Higher = more smooth, lower = less smooth

builderTools.legend.PathBrush.Page1.Title = [TMP] Path Brush
builderTools.legend.PathBrush.Page1.Description = [TMP] The Path Brush Tool allows you to make paths.
builderTools.legend.PathBrush.Page1.DecorateArea = [TMP] Adds half-blocks near level changes to make the path smoother
builderTools.legend.PathBrush.Page1.ShapeArea = [TMP] Draw a path where you're aiming
builderTools.legend.PathBrush.Page2.BlockTip.Title = [TMP] Customizing a Path:
builderTools.legend.PathBrush.Page2.BlockTip.Description = [TMP] You can customize what blocks the path is made out of by dragging and dropping blocks from the inventory into the settings.\n\nYou can also remove blocks by double-clicking on blocks in the setting.
builderTools.legend.PathBrush.Page2.Example1.Title = [TMP] Making a Path:
builderTools.legend.PathBrush.Page2.Example1.Description = [TMP] 1. Look at the ground.\n\
2. Customize the blocks to use for the path by placing blocks in the settings.\n\
3. Hold down the draw key, usually Right-Click, to start drawing the path.\n\
4. Hold down the half-block key, usually Left-Click, to place down half-blocks near un-level area to make them smoother.\n\
6. You now have a path with decorations!
builderTools.legend.PathBrush.Page3.Title = [TMP] Settings
builderTools.legend.PathBrush.Page3.PathBlocks.Title = [TMP] Path Blocks:
builderTools.legend.PathBrush.Page3.PathBlocks.Description = [TMP] - The main blocks the path will be made out of. Comes with a Density slider to control how many to place.
builderTools.legend.PathBrush.Page3.OutlineBlocks.Title = [TMP] Outline Blocks:
builderTools.legend.PathBrush.Page3.OutlineBlocks.Description = [TMP] - The blocks to place on the outline of the path. Comes with a Density slider to control how many to place. Comes with a Width slider to control how wide it will be.
builderTools.legend.PathBrush.Page3.DecorationBlocks.Title = [TMP] Decoration Blocks:
builderTools.legend.PathBrush.Page3.DecorationBlocks.Description = [TMP] - The blocks to add as decorations along the path. Comes with a Density slider to control how many to place. Comes with a Width slider to control how wide it will be.
builderTools.legend.PathBrush.Page3.HalfBlocks.Title = [TMP] Half-Blocks on Path:
builderTools.legend.PathBrush.Page3.HalfBlocks.Description = [TMP] - The half-blocks to be placed near un-level areas to make them smoother.

builderTools.legend.RiverBrush.Page1.Title = [TMP] River Brush
builderTools.legend.RiverBrush.Page1.Description = [TMP] The River Brush Tool allows you to make rivers and oceans.
builderTools.legend.RiverBrush.Page1.DecorateArea = [TMP] Adds decorations where you're aiming
builderTools.legend.RiverBrush.Page1.ShapeArea = [TMP] Draw a river where you're aiming
builderTools.legend.RiverBrush.Page2.BlockTip.Title = [TMP] Customizing a River:
builderTools.legend.RiverBrush.Page2.BlockTip.Description = [TMP] You can customize what blocks the river is made out of by dragging and dropping blocks from the inventory into the settings.\n\nYou can also remove blocks by double-clicking on blocks in the setting.
builderTools.legend.RiverBrush.Page2.Example1.Title = [TMP] Making a River/Waterfall:
builderTools.legend.RiverBrush.Page2.Example1.Description = [TMP] 1. Look at a surface.\n\
2. Customize the blocks to use for the river by placing blocks in the settings.\n\
3. Hold down the draw key, usually Right-Click, to start drawing the river.\n\
4. Hold down the decoration key, usually Left-Click, to place down decorations on the side of the river, under the water, and on top of the water.\n\
5. You now have a river, and or waterfall!
builderTools.legend.RiverBrush.Page3.Title = [TMP] Settings
builderTools.legend.RiverBrush.Page3.FluidMaterial.Title = [TMP] Fluid Material:
builderTools.legend.RiverBrush.Page3.FluidMaterial.Description = [TMP] - The fluid material the river will be made out of.
builderTools.legend.RiverBrush.Page3.SurfaceBlocks.Title = [TMP] Blocks above Fluid:
builderTools.legend.RiverBrush.Page3.SurfaceBlocks.Description = [TMP] - The blocks to place on the side and under the fluid of the river. Comes with a Density slider to control how many to place. Comes with a Width slider to control how wide it will be.
builderTools.legend.RiverBrush.Page3.SubsurfaceBlocks.Title = [TMP] Blocks under Fluid:
builderTools.legend.RiverBrush.Page3.SubsurfaceBlocks.Description = [TMP] - The blocks to place under the fluid of the river. Comes with a Density slider to control how many to place.
builderTools.legend.RiverBrush.Page3.UnderDecorations.Title = [TMP] Decorations under Fluid:
builderTools.legend.RiverBrush.Page3.UnderDecorations.Description = [TMP] - The decorations to under the fluid. Comes with a Density slider to control how many to place.
builderTools.legend.RiverBrush.Page3.SideDecorations.Title = [TMP] Decorations on side of Fluid:
builderTools.legend.RiverBrush.Page3.SideDecorations.Description = [TMP] - The decorations to add on the side of the river. Comes with a Density slider to control how many to place.
builderTools.legend.RiverBrush.Page3.TopDecorations.Title = [TMP] Decorations on top of the Fluid:
builderTools.legend.RiverBrush.Page3.TopDecorations.Description = [TMP] - The decorations to add on the top of the river. Comes with a Density slider to control how many to place.

builderTools.legend.SpiralBrush.Page1.Title = [TMP] Spiral Brush
builderTools.legend.SpiralBrush.Page1.Description = [TMP] The Spiral Brush Tool allows you to make spirals and circular patterns.
builderTools.legend.SpiralBrush.Page1.ShapeArea = [TMP] Place a spiral where you're aiming
builderTools.legend.SpiralBrush.Page2.BlockTip.Title = [TMP] Customizing a Spiral:
builderTools.legend.SpiralBrush.Page2.BlockTip.Description = [TMP] You can customize what blocks the spiral is made out of by dragging and dropping blocks from the inventory into the settings.\n\nYou can also remove blocks by double-clicking on blocks in the setting.
builderTools.legend.SpiralBrush.Page2.Example1.Title = [TMP] Making a Custom Spiral:
builderTools.legend.SpiralBrush.Page2.Example1.Description = [TMP] 1. Look at a surface.\n\
2. Customize the blocks to use for the spiral by placing blocks in the settings.\n\
3. Change the Number of Points to be what you need. Higher = more points in the spiral, Lower = less points in the spiral.\n\
4. Change the Radius to be 15. This will make it wide enough to see what the tool does.\n\
5. If you want a spiral going upward, change the Vertical Spacing to be higher than 0.\n\
6. Change which way the spiral is drawn by checking the Flip, Rotate Direction, or Invert Direction boxes.\n\
7. You can also add smoothing to the spiral by changing the Smoothness to be higher than 0.\n\
8. You can also choose to Hollow Center to make the center of the spiral made of air.\n\
9. You now have a spiral!
builderTools.legend.SpiralBrush.Page3.Title = [TMP] Settings
builderTools.legend.SpiralBrush.Page3.NumberPoints.Title = [TMP] Number of Points:
builderTools.legend.SpiralBrush.Page3.NumberPoints.Description = [TMP] - The number of points on the spiral.
builderTools.legend.SpiralBrush.Page3.Radius.Title = [TMP] Radius:
builderTools.legend.SpiralBrush.Page3.Radius.Description = [TMP] - The radius of the spiral, which is how wide it will be.
builderTools.legend.SpiralBrush.Page3.VerticalSpacing.Title = [TMP] Vertical Spacing:
builderTools.legend.SpiralBrush.Page3.VerticalSpacing.Description = [TMP] - How far apart each point in the spiral is from each other, which is how tall it will be.
builderTools.legend.SpiralBrush.Page3.Flip.Title = [TMP] Flip
builderTools.legend.SpiralBrush.Page3.Flip.Description = [TMP] - Flips the order the spiral is drawn.
builderTools.legend.SpiralBrush.Page3.RotateDirection.Title = [TMP] Rotate Direction
builderTools.legend.SpiralBrush.Page3.RotateDirection.Description = [TMP] - Rotates the spiral 180 degrees.
builderTools.legend.SpiralBrush.Page3.InvertDirection.Title = [TMP] Invert Direction
builderTools.legend.SpiralBrush.Page3.InvertDirection.Description = [TMP] - Inverts the direction the spiral is drawn.
builderTools.legend.SpiralBrush.Page3.Smoothness.Title = [TMP] Smoothness
builderTools.legend.SpiralBrush.Page3.Smoothness.Description = [TMP] - Controls how smooth the spiral will be. Higher = more smooth, Lower = less smooth.
builderTools.legend.SpiralBrush.Page3.HollowCenter.Title = [TMP] Hollow Center
builderTools.legend.SpiralBrush.Page3.HollowCenter.Description = [TMP] - If enabled replaces the center of the spiral with air from where you clicked.

builderTools.legend.RevolveTool.Page1.Title = [TMP] Revolve Tool
builderTools.legend.RevolveTool.Page1.Description = [TMP] The Revolve Tool allows you to rotate and paste, a selection. This tool will only work if a selection has been made.
builderTools.legend.RevolveTool.Page1.ShapeArea = [TMP] Does the revolve. Depending on what settings you are using, it will do the revolve around where you are aiming, or yourself.
builderTools.legend.RevolveTool.Page2.Example1.Title = [TMP] Revolving with the Brush:
builderTools.legend.RevolveTool.Page2.Example1.Description = [TMP] 1. Make a selection that you want to have revolved.\n\
2. Equip the Revolve Tool.\n\
3. Set settings to what you want.\n\
4. Aim the brush to where you want the selection to be revolved around.\n\
5. Press the revolve key, usually Right-Click.\n\
6. You now have revolved your selection!
builderTools.legend.RevolveTool.Page2.Example2.Title = [TMP] Making a Full Circle around Yourself:
builderTools.legend.RevolveTool.Page2.Example2.Description = [TMP] 1. Make a selection that you want to have revolved.\n\
2. Equip the Revolve Tool.\n\
3. Set the Fully Revolve setting to checked, and change the Target to Player (Self).\n\
4. Move yourself so you are some blocks away from your selection.\n\
5. Press the revolve key, usually Right-Click.\n\
6. You now fully revolved the selection around yourself!
builderTools.legend.RevolveTool.Page3.Title = [TMP] Settings
builderTools.legend.RevolveTool.Page3.Sampling.Title = [TMP] Fill Strategy:
builderTools.legend.RevolveTool.Page3.Sampling.Description = [TMP] - The strategy to fill holes in the revolve. Revolving can sometimes leave holes, this will attempt to fill those holes.
builderTools.legend.RevolveTool.Page3.FullyRevolve.Title = [TMP] Fully Revolve:
builderTools.legend.RevolveTool.Page3.FullyRevolve.Description = [TMP] - Will revolve the selection entirely in a circle. This will ignore the Place Count and entirely revolve the selection.
builderTools.legend.RevolveTool.Page3.PlaceCount.Title = [TMP] Paste Count:
builderTools.legend.RevolveTool.Page3.PlaceCount.Description = [TMP] - Controls how many times to paste the selection in the revolve. For example, if this set to 5 then the selection will paste 5 times.
builderTools.legend.RevolveTool.Page3.CenterAround.Title = [TMP] Center Around:
builderTools.legend.RevolveTool.Page3.CenterAround.Description = [TMP] - Controls the target to revolve around. Brush Target = revolve around where the brush is aimed, Player (Self) = revolves around where you are.
builderTools.legend.RevolveTool.Page3.UseCustomDistance.Title = [TMP] Use Custom Radius:
builderTools.legend.RevolveTool.Page3.UseCustomDistance.Description = [TMP] - Pastes and revolves the selection where aimed, and uses Custom Radius to control the spacing from the center.
builderTools.legend.RevolveTool.Page3.PlaceDistance.Title = [TMP] Custom Radius:
builderTools.legend.RevolveTool.Page3.PlaceDistance.Description = [TMP] - The radius to control the spacing between the center and the revolve points. Higher = more wide, Lower = less wide.
builderTools.legend.RevolveTool.Page4.Title = [TMP] Settings (2/2)

