builderTools.legend.LineBrush.Page1.SnapToAngles = Hold to enable snapping to different 45° angles
builderTools.legend.LineBrush.Page1.EditInventoryProperties = Edit materials, size, and other properties from the inventory

builderTools.legend.MachinimaTool.Page1.Title = Getting Started
builderTools.legend.MachinimaTool.Page1.Description = Create keyframed animations using actors, cameras, particles, sounds, and more! Perfect for cinematics and cutscenes.
builderTools.legend.MachinimaTool.Page1.OpensMenu = Open Machinima Editor UI
builderTools.legend.MachinimaTool.Page1.BaseCommand = Base command for all machinima operations
builderTools.legend.MachinimaTool.Page1.Scenes = Scenes\n\
A Scene is a container for your machinima. It stores all actors, keyframes, and settings.
builderTools.legend.MachinimaTool.Page1.CreatingFirstScene = Creating your first Scene\n\
1. Find a nice spot for your machinima\n\
2. Open the Machinima Menu\n\
3. Click the + icon to create a new Scene\n\
4. Add your first Actor!
builderTools.legend.MachinimaTool.Page1.Actors = Actors\n\
An Actor is a keyframe-animatable object. See the next page for actor types.
builderTools.legend.MachinimaTool.Page1.AddingCameraActor = Adding a Camera Actor\n\
1. Position yourself where you want the camera\n\
2. Open the Machinima Menu\n\
3. Click the + icon under the scene list\n\
4. Select "Camera" from the dropdown\n\
5. You can now click on the camera to reposition it, and press C to toggle the camera view!

builderTools.legend.MachinimaTool.Page2.Title = Actor Types
builderTools.legend.MachinimaTool.Page2.Description = Different actor types serve different purposes in your machinima. They're all animateable objects that allow you to control position, rotation, and other values. Actors are added via the Machinima Menu
builderTools.legend.MachinimaTool.Page2.CameraHeader = Camera
builderTools.legend.MachinimaTool.Page2.CameraDesc = Allows you to move a camera across paths and animate various settings such as FOV and Speed.
builderTools.legend.MachinimaTool.Page2.EntityHeader = Entity
builderTools.legend.MachinimaTool.Page2.EntityDesc = Animated characters with models. Supports body/head rotation and animation events.
builderTools.legend.MachinimaTool.Page2.PlayerHeader = Player
builderTools.legend.MachinimaTool.Page2.PlayerDesc = Similar to Entity, references the local player.
builderTools.legend.MachinimaTool.Page2.ReferenceHeader = Reference
builderTools.legend.MachinimaTool.Page2.ReferenceDesc = Invisible marker points. Useful for targeting and reference positions. Allows you to set camera targets to track the points.
builderTools.legend.MachinimaTool.Page2.ItemHeader = Item
builderTools.legend.MachinimaTool.Page2.ItemDesc = Displays items in the world. Can be positioned and animated.
builderTools.legend.MachinimaTool.Page2.AddActorCommand = Command: .mach actor add [type] [name]\n\
Types: camera, entity, player, ref, item

builderTools.legend.MachinimaTool.Page3.Title = Playback Controls
builderTools.legend.MachinimaTool.Page3.Description = Playback controls let you preview your scene by animating all actors along their keyframe paths. Use these to scrub through time, jump between keyframes, and test your animations. Every frame will update all the actors along their keyframe paths, running the animations.
builderTools.legend.MachinimaTool.Page3.TogglePause = Toggle Play / Pause
builderTools.legend.MachinimaTool.Page3.ContinuousPlayback = Toggle Continuous Playback (loops)
builderTools.legend.MachinimaTool.Page3.AutoRestart = Toggle Auto-Restart on scene end
builderTools.legend.MachinimaTool.Page3.RestartScene = Restart Scene from beginning
builderTools.legend.MachinimaTool.Page3.EndScene = Skip to final frame
builderTools.legend.MachinimaTool.Page3.NavigationTitle = Frame Navigation:
builderTools.legend.MachinimaTool.Page3.FrameScrub = Scrub through frames (hold for continuous)
builderTools.legend.MachinimaTool.Page3.JumpKeyframe = Jump to previous / next keyframe point
builderTools.legend.MachinimaTool.Page3.SpeedModifiers = Hold SHIFT for 2x speed, ALT for 0.5x speed

builderTools.legend.MachinimaTool.Page4.Title = Keyframe Editing
builderTools.legend.MachinimaTool.Page4.Description = Keyframes define an actor's position, rotation, and settings at specific points in time. The system interpolates between keyframes to create smooth animation paths. Add keyframes to create motion, edit them to fine-tune timing and positioning.
builderTools.legend.MachinimaTool.Page4.AddKeyframe = Add new keyframe at the end of the actor's track, extending the animation
builderTools.legend.MachinimaTool.Page4.AddAtCurrentFrame = Insert a keyframe at the current playback position
builderTools.legend.MachinimaTool.Page4.CopyKeyframe = Copy selected keyframe settings to paste on another actor or frame
builderTools.legend.MachinimaTool.Page4.DeleteKeyframe = Remove the keyframe you're hovering over
builderTools.legend.MachinimaTool.Page4.EditKeyframe = Open gizmo to adjust keyframe position and rotation
builderTools.legend.MachinimaTool.Page4.MoveActor = Reposition the entire actor path as a whole
builderTools.legend.MachinimaTool.Page4.EditFrameTime = Change when this keyframe occurs in the timeline
builderTools.legend.MachinimaTool.Page4.AdjustFrameTime = Nudge keyframe timing earlier or later

builderTools.legend.MachinimaTool.Page5.Title = Mouse Interactions
builderTools.legend.MachinimaTool.Page5.Description = Click on keyframe nodes in the world to interact:
builderTools.legend.MachinimaTool.Page5.SelectKeyframe = Select keyframe (enter Free Move mode)
builderTools.legend.MachinimaTool.Page5.JumpToKeyframe = Set as active and jump to frame
builderTools.legend.MachinimaTool.Page5.GizmoTitle = Gizmo Controls:
builderTools.legend.MachinimaTool.Page5.TranslationGizmo = Open Translation Gizmo (axis-locked)
builderTools.legend.MachinimaTool.Page5.RotationGizmo = Open Rotation Gizmo (head/body)
builderTools.legend.MachinimaTool.Page5.FreeMoveTitle = Free Move Mode:
builderTools.legend.MachinimaTool.Page5.FreeMoveDescription = Left-click to confirm position, Right-click to cancel.\n\
Hold SHIFT to snap to surfaces at distance.\n\
Hold ALT to ignore surface snapping.

builderTools.legend.MachinimaTool.Page6.Title = Selection Modes
builderTools.legend.MachinimaTool.Page6.Description = Selection modes determine what gets moved when you use transformation tools. Choose the right mode based on what you want to reposition.
builderTools.legend.MachinimaTool.Page6.CycleMode = Cycle between selection modes
builderTools.legend.MachinimaTool.Page6.KeyframeModeTitle = Keyframe Mode (Default)
builderTools.legend.MachinimaTool.Page6.KeyframeModeDesc = Moves only the selected keyframe. Use this for precise adjustments to individual points along an actor's path without affecting other keyframes.
builderTools.legend.MachinimaTool.Page6.ActorModeTitle = Actor Mode
builderTools.legend.MachinimaTool.Page6.ActorModeDesc = Moves all keyframes for the selected actor together. The entire path shifts as one unit, preserving the shape of the animation.
builderTools.legend.MachinimaTool.Page6.SceneModeTitle = Scene Mode
builderTools.legend.MachinimaTool.Page6.SceneModeDesc = Moves the entire scene origin, shifting all actors and their paths together. Useful for relocating your whole machinima to a different area.

builderTools.legend.MachinimaTool.Page7.Title = Display & Origin
